+## 1. Vision reconstruction
+
+Boss is trying to build a complete paid German A1 web-app course for Malayali adult beginners.
+
+Plain version:
+
+Adipoli German should take someone from zero German to a confident Goethe A1 attempt through short, phone-first, Kerala-rooted story missions. The learner follows Kuttan’s Kerala-to-Germany pressure, but the learner is not watching a cartoon or browsing a library. They hear German, understand it, answer aloud, repair one real beginner mistake, write/type only when it helps A1, and leave with a concrete ability win.
+
+The course should feel like:
+- made for Malayalis, not generic German learners;
+- exam-serious, not casual phrase entertainment;
+- warm and culturally familiar, not childish;
+- audio-first and production-first, not text-first dashboards;
+- self-guiding enough that Boss does not have to explain where to click;
+- affordable, but not cheap-feeling.
+
+Core product promise:
+
+German A1 for Malayalis through short story missions: hear it, say it, fix it, use it, and prepare for Goethe.
+
+Hard rule:
+
+If a student can finish a route without hearing, speaking, writing/typing, or proving a Goethe-relevant ability, the route does not match the vision.
+
+## 2. Non-negotiables
+
+1. Malayali/Kerala identity
+- A1 physically happens in Kerala.
+- Kuttan stays in Kerala during A1.
+- Germany appears as goal, dream, cousin video call, exam rehearsal, form simulation, or learner imagination.
+- Manglish is a bridge for real learning mistakes, not a joke layer.
+- Kerala context must do work: Goethe Kochi, family pressure, migration dream, documentation anxiety, exam prep, cousin in Germany, home study, Kerala classroom/cafe scenes.
+
+2. Goethe A1 seriousness
+- Every module must map to at least one A1 ability.
+- Hören, Lesen, Schreiben, and Sprechen must all be practiced.
+- Hören needs real audio, not visible text pretending to be listening.
+- Schreiben needs form-filling and short-message production.
+- Sprechen needs repeated self-intro, question, request, spelling, and response practice.
+- Entertainment is allowed only when it strengthens a survival/exam skill.
+
+3. Adult-safe tone
+- Kuttan can be relatable and warm.
+- Kuttan/Appu cannot make the paid product feel like a kids app.
+- Appu stays silent UI flavor unless Boss explicitly changes it.
+- Public naming is still a product risk: “Kuttan” is culturally warm but may feel childish to some buyers.
+
+4. Real audio
+- No browser SpeechSynthesis on reviewable German paths.
+- Audio must be real files, served over HTTP, with browser playback proof.
+- Audio UI must show duration/progress or equivalent reviewable playback state.
+- Learner turn must unlock after the relevant audio finishes, not after a fake “heard” click.
